Package fetchData

Class DataReader

java.lang.Object
fetchData.DataReader
public class DataReader
extends java.lang.Object
A class used to retrieve data from the World Bank Server.

The primary purpose of this class is, given a data type, country, and range of years, to retrieve a DataObject containing the values corresponding to the information available on the World Bank Server. Date: 4/2/2021

Author:
Cameron Arnold

  • Constructor Details

    • DataReader

      public DataReader​(systemSelection selection)
      Constructor

      Creates the DataReader country and year range defined in the provided systemSelection object. Certain data types (ex. CO2 Emissions) can be further retrieved for the country using the getData() method defined below.

      Parameters:
      selection - The selection object containing the country name and years range needed to construct the DataReader.

  • Method Details

    • findCountryISO

      public java.lang.String findCountryISO​(java.lang.String country)
      Returns the ISO name corresponding to the provided country name, using the list of country ISOs found in countryISO.txt

      Effects:
      • None.
      Parameters:
      country - The name of the country to retrieve the ISO name for.
      Returns:
      The ISO name of the provided country.

    • getData

      public DataObject getData​(java.lang.String dataType)
      Returns a DataObject containing the data retrieved from the World Bank Server corresponding to the provided data type (GDP, population, etc), country, starting year, and final year.

      Effects:
      • None.
      Parameters:
      dataType - The WBAPI indicator for the requested data type (ex. "SP.POP.TOTL" for total population)
      Returns:
      A DataObject containing the data retrieved from the World Bank API
